And I felt, with a fear I could not reason.
They watch us, they invade us.
And keep us happy, committing treason.
To a King we didn't deserve.
To a Son who waits weeping.
That I knew, from knowledge gained while sleeping.`</field></block></value><next><block type="array_insertAt" id="A1DbRWso}4-;nJuCV.k0"><value name="list"><block type="variables_get" id="e6w0vE*AIPk3iQ-)N|mW"><field name="VAR" id="o/Sm,,BA$/I:7Gqb$umW">death_quotes</field></block></value><value name="index"><block type="lists_length" id=".wH@rLRkYbQBvvNkh|j["><value name="VALUE"><block type="variables_get" id="!cg!-RYh|Pt7Jzsnic33"><field name="VAR" id="o/Sm,,BA$/I:7Gqb$umW">death_quotes</field></block></value></block></value><value name="value"><block type="typescript_expression" id="RUc8I%k@pFY38`o~#!W,"><field name="EXPRESSION">`TO TAKE THE DEAD
